Eric, if he's
not hungry--

49:00.187 --> 49:03.272
you don't have
to eat, Deon, okay?

49:03.315 --> 49:05.483
But I did make
some of that pecan pie.

49:05.567 --> 49:06.692
You want some?

49:06.777 --> 49:08.110
Pecan pie everybody?

49:08.195 --> 49:09.820
I love pecan pie.

49:15.786 --> 49:18.955
Bernie, you gotta
at least let him
get his own stuff.

49:18.997 --> 49:20.456
I mean, he's been
home for two weeks.

49:20.540 --> 49:21.874
He's just been
sitting on his ass.

49:21.959 --> 49:23.542
Look, you have
to be patient.

49:23.627 --> 49:25.211
It takes time.
I know Deon.

49:25.295 --> 49:27.463
He's going to do things
in his own time.

49:27.547 --> 49:29.674
He goes to take a dump,
you're there to help him.

49:29.758 --> 49:31.092
Okay, that's disgusting,
that's enough.

49:31.176 --> 49:32.677
I don't feel like
hearing that.

49:32.761 --> 49:34.971
Look, the cancer
knocked him down.

49:35.055 --> 49:36.681
We just have to
be patient.

49:36.765 --> 49:38.224
It's not how many times
you get knocked down.

49:38.308 --> 49:40.267
It's how many times
you get back up.

49:40.352 --> 49:42.269
Would you please stop
with that ra-ra football
bullshit?

49:42.354 --> 49:44.313
I know my boy,
I know he's gonna
be okay.

49:44.356 --> 49:46.816
He's not a boy.
And you can't teach
him how to be a man.

49:46.858 --> 49:48.901
The goddamn president
of the United States
was raised by a woman.

49:48.986 --> 49:50.569
Barack Obama
was raised
by single mothers.

49:50.654 --> 49:52.697
He don't play
football, do he?

49:52.781 --> 49:55.157
He play basketball.
Shut the--.

49:55.242 --> 49:58.452
Look, get the pecan pie.
I'll get the dishes.

50:01.331 --> 50:02.915
I have finals
and stuff

50:03.000 --> 50:04.917
so I think I'll
be heading out.

50:05.002 --> 50:05.876
I'll walk you out.

50:05.961 --> 50:08.504
I got it.

50:08.547 --> 50:14.677
[groan]

50:14.720 --> 50:17.430
Sorry about that.
That was embarrassing.

50:17.514 --> 50:19.557
No, no,
it's all good.

50:19.641 --> 50:22.518
They're all trying
to help you from
their own perspective.

50:22.561 --> 50:24.186
What about you?

50:24.271 --> 50:25.855
What about me?

50:25.939 --> 50:29.025
Things different now
that I got sick?

50:29.067 --> 50:31.944
No. It's been tough.

50:32.029 --> 50:33.404
It's just--

50:33.488 --> 50:35.614
You interested
in somebody else?

50:35.699 --> 50:37.700
Not at all.

50:37.743 --> 50:39.577
I've just got--
[cell phone rings]

50:39.661 --> 50:42.705
I'm sorry.

50:45.292 --> 50:46.792
It's my mother.

50:46.877 --> 50:48.419
I'll call you later.

50:48.503 --> 50:49.420
Okay.

51:12.903 --> 51:29.585
[groan]

51:29.628 --> 51:30.920
Two.

51:31.004 --> 51:33.089
(Mom)
Deon!

51:33.173 --> 51:35.424
Seventeen.

51:35.467 --> 51:36.884
Eighteen.

51:36.968 --> 51:40.012
[clapping]
That is great!

51:40.097 --> 51:41.806
[groan]

51:41.890 --> 51:44.683
You couldn't even
do that this time
last week.

51:44.768 --> 51:47.937
Look, I just came
to apologize.

51:48.021 --> 51:50.189
Eric acted
so damn crazy.

51:50.273 --> 51:53.776
You know, fussing
in front of--Sharon
and everything.

51:57.114 --> 51:58.614
Do you like her?

51:58.698 --> 52:02.034
[chuckle]

52:02.119 --> 52:03.536
Yeah.

52:06.706 --> 52:09.125
I see you
boxed up the TV.

52:09.167 --> 52:12.378
Well, we just
have to send some
of this stuff back,

52:12.462 --> 52:15.965
that's all. It's
just a delay.

52:16.007 --> 52:18.467
I know how much
you like that
flat screen.

52:18.552 --> 52:23.305
I do but it's just
a hiccup, that's all.

52:23.348 --> 52:25.850
Sweetheart, you gonna get
better in your own time

52:25.934 --> 52:29.186
and we gonna get rid
of this crappy ass
little house

52:29.271 --> 52:31.564
and we gonna be
down in Miami,

52:31.648 --> 52:33.649
livin' it, honey.

52:33.733 --> 52:39.572
And we gonna get
everything we deserve
in life, you'll see.

52:39.656 --> 52:44.243
I'm sorry, Ma.

52:44.327 --> 52:46.162
I didn't mean
to get sick.

52:46.204 --> 52:48.914
Oh, sweetie.
Don't apologize
for that.

52:48.999 --> 52:50.583
What you sayin'?

52:50.667 --> 52:54.003
I don't know why
this is happening.

52:54.045 --> 52:57.423
I mean, I didn't do nothing
to nobody, I didn't
do anything.

52:57.507 --> 53:02.428
Well--it's a challenge.

53:02.512 --> 53:05.514
It's just another
challenge, that's all.

53:05.557 --> 53:07.558
And you will be fine.

53:07.642 --> 53:14.440
We will be fine,
I promise you.

53:14.524 --> 53:16.358
Why is God
doing this to me?

53:16.443 --> 53:19.486
Oh, no, no.
Don't say that,
sweetheart. Don't.

53:19.571 --> 53:26.202
[both weep]

53:26.244 --> 53:29.246
[phone ringing]

53:29.331 --> 53:30.247
[beep]

53:30.332 --> 53:31.957
Hello?

53:32.042 --> 53:33.667
(Mom)
Hey, baby.
What's up?

53:33.752 --> 53:35.294
Hey, Momma.
I'm just
checking out

53:35.378 --> 53:37.546
the status of
some applications.

53:37.589 --> 53:39.465
I thought you said the
party was supposed
to end early.

53:39.549 --> 53:42.551
Well, it was, but
one of my servers
didn't show up.

53:42.636 --> 53:44.136
So I had
to fill in.

53:44.221 --> 53:45.387
I've been on
my feet all night.

53:45.472 --> 53:47.473
[laughs]

53:47.557 --> 53:49.725
I can stop and
get some pizza.
What do you want?

53:49.768 --> 53:51.894
Oh, I'm the
only one home.

53:51.937 --> 53:53.229
Eric and Deon
aren't here.

53:53.313 --> 53:54.730
They're not there?

53:54.773 --> 53:56.565
Well, where the
hell did they go?

53:56.650 --> 53:58.943
I don't know.
They haven't been
here for hours.

53:59.027 --> 54:00.986
I called both
their phones
but nobody answers.

54:01.071 --> 54:03.489
Look, just meet
me outside in
five minutes.

54:03.573 --> 54:04.490
I'll be right there.

54:04.574 --> 54:05.574
Okay.

54:05.617 --> 54:07.076
Bye.

54:07.118 --> 54:08.244
[beep]

54:14.584 --> 54:16.085
How long ago
did they leave?

54:16.169 --> 54:18.254
I don't know.
Hours ago, Ma.

54:18.338 --> 54:21.006
Oh, Lord.

54:21.091 --> 54:23.592
Damn. What's your
brother's cell
phone number?

54:23.635 --> 54:26.637
Oh, it's in the phone.
It's in the phone.

54:26.721 --> 54:29.932
Ma.
Mom, look!

54:29.975 --> 54:32.142
What the hell
is he doin'?

54:32.227 --> 54:34.311
Jesus. Pull over.
Just pull over.

54:34.396 --> 54:36.855
Look at that time,
44 seconds, that
ain't shit!

54:36.940 --> 54:38.857
My grandmother could
do that in her wheelchair!

54:38.942 --> 54:40.442
I'm trying.

54:40.485 --> 54:41.902
Get those knees up.
Don't try, do it!

54:41.987 --> 54:43.612
You gotta get them.
Go get them.

54:43.655 --> 54:44.947
Everything you ever
wanted is on the line.

54:44.990 --> 54:46.073
(Mom)
Eric!

54:46.157 --> 54:47.700
It's do or die time.

54:47.784 --> 54:48.784
You don't have
to do that,
Deon! Stop!

54:48.868 --> 54:49.743
Deon!

54:49.828 --> 54:51.161
No, no, no.

54:51.246 --> 54:52.246
Don't you fucking
look at them!

54:52.330 --> 54:54.123
I gotta get him!

54:54.165 --> 54:56.083
(Eric)
Don't let them
distract you.

54:56.167 --> 54:58.127
Oh, you want a break?
You wanna run
to Momma?

54:58.169 --> 55:00.087
You wanna cry to your mother
or you wanna play football?

55:00.171 --> 55:01.630
Show me something, Deon.
Show me something!

55:01.715 --> 55:03.048
Eric!

55:03.133 --> 55:05.175
Bernie. Now
you guys stop.

55:05.260 --> 55:06.844
You have no idea
what it takes
to win.

55:06.928 --> 55:09.680
You want it, you gotta
show me something.

55:09.764 --> 55:12.474
You stop it!
Eric! You're
gonna kill him!

55:12.559 --> 55:14.476
- Don't do this!
- He needs to do this!

55:14.561 --> 55:16.603
- What is wrong with you?
- He has got to do this.

55:16.688 --> 55:18.397
- That's enough!
- He's got to do this
on his own.

55:18.481 --> 55:19.857
Bee, you got
no idea!
This is it!

55:19.941 --> 55:21.400
He's passing out!

55:23.486 --> 55:29.658
[indistinct]

55:29.743 --> 55:32.578
(male)
Sorry, guys, you're gonna
have to wait back here.

55:32.662 --> 55:34.330
[distant murmur]

55:50.347 --> 55:52.890
(doctor)
Seems Deon was
working late tonight.

55:52.974 --> 55:56.185
Your son, he had a--
a heart arrhythmia,

55:56.227 --> 55:58.520
and that depleted
him of his oxygen.

55:58.605 --> 55:59.938
Is he gonna
be okay?

56:00.023 --> 56:01.357
Yeah, he's stablized
for now.

56:01.441 --> 56:03.650
What the hell happened?

56:03.735 --> 56:05.778
Because the specialist
on duty said we need to
get him up and active.

56:05.862 --> 56:08.447
Now he's got pro football
tryouts in less than
a month.

56:08.531 --> 56:11.950
Professional football?
You kidding me?

56:12.035 --> 56:14.078
He can't play football.
He's got a tumor

56:14.162 --> 56:16.955
a centimeter away
from his heart.

56:17.040 --> 56:20.959
Your son, he's never
ever gonna become a
professional athlete.

56:21.044 --> 56:23.545
He's lucky if he
ever rides a
bike again.

56:28.385 --> 56:31.595
You did this.

56:31.679 --> 56:33.722
You did this!

56:40.647 --> 56:42.064
These motherfuckers
don't know shit!

56:42.148 --> 56:43.899
Everything they
told us was wrong.

56:43.942 --> 56:45.984
We oughtta sue
that hospital
for malpractice.

56:46.069 --> 56:47.319
We should
sue the university.

56:47.404 --> 56:48.821
They tested him
every year.

56:48.905 --> 56:50.364
They had to know
this was coming.

56:50.448 --> 56:52.116
That would call
for lawyers, Eric.

56:52.200 --> 56:53.909
Lawyers cost money.
Who's gonna pay for that?

56:53.993 --> 56:55.661
What you trying to say?
I didn't pay for shit?

56:55.745 --> 56:57.079
I leveraged my
garage, baby.

56:57.163 --> 56:58.622
I could lose
my business.

56:58.706 --> 57:00.416
I put it on
the line for
your son.

57:00.500 --> 57:01.917
Please don't talk to me
about money when they're

57:01.960 --> 57:03.502
about to foreclose on
this house.

57:03.586 --> 57:05.587
Everybody knows about
your little dream

57:05.672 --> 57:08.006
to ride on my son's coat
tails for the fame
you didn't get.

57:08.091 --> 57:09.633
Your little dream
to manage my son.

57:09.717 --> 57:11.510
Well, Eric there's
nobody to manage now.

57:11.594 --> 57:13.220
Who you gonna
manage now?

57:13.304 --> 57:15.305
Know when the best
times of my life were?

57:15.390 --> 57:16.598
When I was on
that football field.

57:16.641 --> 57:18.851
I don't care.

57:18.935 --> 57:20.602
I wanted your boy
to have something
good to look back on.

57:20.687 --> 57:22.187
I'm tired of all your
loser football stories.

57:22.272 --> 57:23.939
Every step of the way,
you blocked me.

57:24.023 --> 57:26.108
He coulda done it.
He had the talent.

57:26.192 --> 57:28.110
And remember,
when you ran off
his real daddy,

57:28.153 --> 57:30.529
truth be told,
I was there.

57:30.613 --> 57:34.158
If that man couldn't see
that he had two beautiful
sons and a beautiful wife,

57:34.242 --> 57:36.201
that was his
goddamn problem.

57:36.286 --> 57:38.537
Now let me tell
you something.

57:38.621 --> 57:40.789
Me and my sons were fine
long before you came
into this mix

57:40.832 --> 57:43.167
and we'll be fine
long after you leave.

57:43.251 --> 57:44.960
So you can just hit
the road right now

57:45.003 --> 57:46.879
because it's empty.
There's no money.

57:46.963 --> 57:48.797
Overdrawn,
insufficient funds.

57:48.840 --> 57:50.883
There's no pot of gold
at the end of this rainbow,

57:50.967 --> 57:51.967
so get the fuck
outta here!

57:52.010 --> 57:52.968
Okay!

57:53.052 --> 57:54.678
I'm right here!

57:54.762 --> 57:56.889
You talking about me
like I'm dead already.

57:56.973 --> 57:58.515
I'll pay this back.

57:58.600 --> 58:00.851
I'll find
a way to pay
everybody back.

58:00.935 --> 58:02.144
I'll find a way.

58:11.779 --> 58:13.530
[door opens
and closes]

58:20.330 --> 58:24.041
Hey, I have
an appointment to
see Steve Fisk.

58:28.755 --> 58:30.047
[knocking]

58:30.131 --> 58:31.256
Stephen?

58:31.341 --> 58:32.549
That's me.
You are?

58:32.634 --> 58:33.884
Deon.

58:33.968 --> 58:35.427
Deon, please
have a seat.

58:35.512 --> 58:37.554
What's your last name
and student I D?

58:37.639 --> 58:41.225
Barnes.
Zero five
one five.

58:41.309 --> 58:44.686
I'm sorry, zero
two five one five.

58:44.771 --> 58:48.357
Barnes, Barnes.
Deon Barnes.

58:48.441 --> 58:51.026
You know we used to have
this all star football
player by that same name.

58:51.110 --> 58:53.445
Had an ego
the size of Texas.

58:58.368 --> 58:59.868
Oh, man.

58:59.911 --> 59:02.246
Listen, I'm sorry
about that.

59:02.330 --> 59:04.540
Yeah, just tell me
what I gotta do to
graduate, alright?

59:04.624 --> 59:09.628
Well--it appears
as though you never
actually declared a major.

59:09.712 --> 59:12.214
GPA's at the minimum.

59:12.298 --> 59:14.883
But you dropped out
during fall semester.

59:14.926 --> 59:17.594
Probably looking
at the full two years.

59:17.679 --> 59:21.390
It's--here
are some
financial aid forms.

59:21.432 --> 59:22.891
See if you can have
those completed and
back to me

59:22.976 --> 59:24.977
later this week, alright?

59:25.061 --> 59:29.439
Financial aid funds?
I'm on a scholarship.

59:29.524 --> 59:32.401
Come on, Julio,
my granddaughter
can run faster than that.

59:32.443 --> 59:35.237
Get the piano off
your back, Jonas!

59:35.321 --> 59:38.740
Let's go!
[indistinct] stride out!

59:38.825 --> 59:42.452
Listen, I heard you
revoked my scholarship.

59:42.537 --> 59:44.454
I didn't have any choice.

59:44.539 --> 59:46.999
Once you dropped
out of school,
it was an NCAA thing.

59:47.083 --> 59:48.917
Nothing else
I could do.

59:49.002 --> 59:51.420
I just wish
you'd told me.

59:51.504 --> 59:54.381
And what would
that have changed?

59:58.094 --> 59:59.845
(coach)
Set.

59:59.929 --> 01:00:01.471
Go!
Bring it!

01:00:01.556 --> 01:00:03.599
Come on, baby!
Let's go!

01:00:03.683 --> 01:00:05.267
[click]

01:00:05.310 --> 01:00:07.603
I thought you were
a running back, Deon.

01:00:07.687 --> 01:00:10.022
That's who gets
all the pretty girls
and make all the money.

01:00:10.106 --> 01:00:12.274
Now give us some
running back time.
Get back down there.

01:00:12.358 --> 01:00:14.776
You got another
one in you?

01:00:14.819 --> 01:00:16.612
(Deon)
Alright.

01:00:16.696 --> 01:00:18.488
(coach)
Just stride out.
stride out.

01:00:18.573 --> 01:00:20.282
This kid's nuts.

01:00:20.325 --> 01:00:21.658
Yeah, he's the
best I've ever seen.

01:00:25.121 --> 01:00:27.331
You know, I can remember
the exact moment

01:00:27.415 --> 01:00:32.461
when I realized that I
wasn't gonna be playing
professional football.

01:00:32.545 --> 01:00:36.715
What are you
gonna do now?

01:00:36.799 --> 01:00:38.383
I don't know.

01:00:38.468 --> 01:00:41.219
Look, if you need a job,

01:00:41.304 --> 01:00:43.472
why don't you come
see me at the end
of the summer.

01:00:43.514 --> 01:00:46.141
I'll see if I can
get you on the staff.

01:00:46.184 --> 01:00:49.061
You'll work with
the running backs,

01:00:49.145 --> 01:00:50.729
keep you close
to the game.

01:00:57.320 --> 01:00:59.946
[sigh]

01:01:02.241 --> 01:01:05.077
Ray. That's the last
drink for you.

01:01:05.161 --> 01:01:06.703
Hey!

01:01:06.788 --> 01:01:09.498
And I called a taxi,
it's on the way.

01:01:09.582 --> 01:01:10.874
Bacardi coke?

01:01:10.958 --> 01:01:13.418
Yeah, make it
a double.

01:01:13.503 --> 01:01:15.504
You girls
talking about me?

01:01:15.546 --> 01:01:19.424
Yeah, about how much
of a red hot stud you are.

01:01:19.509 --> 01:01:20.842
[chuckles]

01:01:20.927 --> 01:01:23.095
So who's
taking me home?

01:01:23.179 --> 01:01:28.016
She is, baby.
I lost the
flip, sorry.

01:01:28.059 --> 01:01:30.977
Respect your elders, now.

01:01:32.230 --> 01:01:35.607
[crash]

01:01:35.692 --> 01:01:37.693
Oh, we gotta get him
out of here.

01:01:37.777 --> 01:01:40.112
We don't have that
kind of insurance.

01:01:40.196 --> 01:01:43.281
When'd you start
smoking again?

01:01:43.366 --> 01:01:48.704
Well, Eric left.

01:01:48.746 --> 01:01:51.415
My son's sick.
The bills are mounting up.

01:01:51.499 --> 01:01:53.250
[sigh]

01:01:53.334 --> 01:01:56.420
And everywhere I look,
I'm in the damn brick wall.

01:01:56.504 --> 01:02:02.050
You know what
I did, I put all
my dreams in one basket.

01:02:02.135 --> 01:02:04.553
Here I am back here
at square one.

01:02:04.595 --> 01:02:08.140
I thought my days
of spoon-feeding
infants was over.

01:02:08.224 --> 01:02:13.395
And I'm here with--what?

01:02:13.479 --> 01:02:16.064
Oh, shit.
Deon!

01:02:16.107 --> 01:02:18.567
Deon!
Wait, baby, wait!

01:02:18.651 --> 01:02:21.111
No!

01:02:21.195 --> 01:02:23.655
Stop, look,
I'm sorry.

01:02:23.740 --> 01:02:28.243
I didn't mean it
like that.
I just--

01:02:28.286 --> 01:02:32.080
Oh!

01:02:32.123 --> 01:02:33.874
I'm sorry.

01:02:44.385 --> 01:02:46.178
Hey, man,
I'm looking for a job.

01:02:46.262 --> 01:02:48.013
You hiring?

01:02:48.097 --> 01:02:51.349
Hey, I'm looking for work.
You guys need any help?

01:03:23.132 --> 01:03:25.467
(Deon)
Hey, Kerry,
what's up?

01:03:25.510 --> 01:03:27.844
Hey, do I--do
I know you?

01:03:27.929 --> 01:03:31.056
Yeah, you--remember
we used to hang out.

01:03:31.140 --> 01:03:35.560
I'm sorry,
I don't remember you.

01:03:52.286 --> 01:03:53.870
(June)
So how
did it go?

01:03:53.955 --> 01:03:57.040
It didn't. I quit
that bullshit ass job.

01:03:57.124 --> 01:03:59.042
Minimum wage, stand
on your feet all day

01:03:59.126 --> 01:04:00.919
cleaning up
after motherfuckers.

01:04:01.003 --> 01:04:03.672
Man, I don't know
how regular people
do that shit.

01:04:03.756 --> 01:04:05.423
To top it off, man,
this chick I used to hit,

01:04:05.508 --> 01:04:07.676
she didn't even
recognize me.

01:04:07.760 --> 01:04:09.261
What?

01:04:09.345 --> 01:04:11.680
I don't need
that bullshit.

01:04:11.722 --> 01:04:13.682
Man, fuck them
bitches, man.

01:04:13.766 --> 01:04:15.934
